3 REASONS PEOPLE GO OVER BUDGET WHEN BUILDING A HOME 
•

•

•

1. Lack of vision for your future home.

2. Not having a realistic budget. 

3. Accepting a misquoted scope of work bid. 

•

•

•

#IMPORTANT If you are in the market for a resale home that’s pre-existing and plan to renovate, lowest bid is not always the best choice. If the goal is saving money, you’ll find that bait and switch is very common with some contractors. If you are not careful or working with an experienced professional it’s easy to go WAY over that initial bid as you get into the thick of your project. At that point, unfortunately, it will be too late to change course and you will have no choice but to continue increasing your budget.

•

•

#SaveThisPost So keep this in mind… if you get three or more bids from builders and one bid is significantly lower than the others, I recommend that you really give thought to how this bid was determined before you sign on the dotted line with that contractor. OR CALL ME, SIS HAS YOUR BACK 👊🏾💕
